        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">VenrWrath, maybe it was thought about but it still had problems and the problem in my opinion wasn't how rare it was.</P><P>My problem was how basically easy our quest is. Even now with the silk cape drop as rare as it is, our actual quest is something any half decent guild can do.</P><P>Raid chardok, kill a few golems in fear, clear hate once or twice and raid to the fourth isle of sky.</P><P>In essence it is too easy. It isn't a real challenge that would keep the numbers of the epic down like it should be. Instead the challenge lies purely in random drops which in my opinion makes the quest more random then something that took time and an effort. I know necros who said to me, "oh yeah if I get the cape in sky then I'll just finish the rest off in a day or so"</P><P>In my opinion this isn't how the quest should have been. It should've been challenges and maybe lots of them. A quest that took a month to complete and a lot of team work and man power. That is what I think of as an "epic" quest.</P><P>Camping something, or raiding something and hoping for a random drop doesn't seem to constitute a well thought out quest.</P><P>Like if they made it so you had to raid to the seventh isle of sky, then spawned a dragon type mob that you had to kill and take a piece back to Kazen... that would be far from easy, cool, but possible to do.</P><P>At the same time I understand why VI didn't do this. They want to make things seem possible for people who aren't in large raid guilds, or are a casual player.</P><P>Hehe the more I think about it the more I would hate to have a job in VI. To find a balance on quests like this without making it too out of reach, yet still be able to make it mildly rare...</P><P>The problem with a spawn type quest in my opinion is that any uber guild then will be able to spend the time and equip every single one of their members with the item. Like the cleric epic for example. And this as we know does not make it rare, it just means if you're in a good guild you can get one.</P><P>Or you have a random type quest (like our quest) and it keeps the numbers down on the server but makes it so that basically anybody lucky enough to get a drop nearly automatically gets their epic.</P><P>I'm not sure where the happy medium would be.</P><P>Gylgesh Gloomtouch,<BR>54th Necro of the Heroic Few<BR>Morell-Thule<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
