        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Lady Vox...<BR>You say I am full of envy but maybe I am worried at having my unique status ruined? Does this make sense?</P><P>First of all I am not worried about having my unique status ruined because I don't have my epic. And I'm not sure what I would be in envy over any how? Envy over people with their epics, or envious of those without it?</P><P>Either way I think you misunderstood my post. First of all I already said fixing this drop was a GOOD thing. My previous post was basic speculation on what I think is wrong with quests in eq.</P><P>I made the first statement of saying I thought this quest couldn't have been thought through in the first place.</P><P>VenrWrath said he thought it was because originally there was only supposed to be a few epics per server.</P><P>I replied with: true enough perhaps our quest was thought through but this is what I think are the problems with the quests in EQ.</P><P>1) They are bad (like our quest) in that they revolve around obscene random drops<BR>2) They are quests that involve spawning something (like the cleric epic) in which any cleric can get one with not too much effort depending on the ragefire spawn<BR>3) they are too difficult in that only 2 uber guilds will be able to do it and they will outfit every one of their characters with those items</P><P>So the question was: where is the happy medium? I think VI would actually like to see items that every single person running around didn't have one, yet were still attainable and fun to do. I think they would like to see maybe 25% of a certain class inbetween 50-60 to have an item like this. But they don't want to see it limited to uber only but still want to keep it rare and difficult to obtain.</P><P>That was the gist of my post, it was just meant as analytical speculation (neither right nor wrong, just thoughts) of why certain quests sucked and certain quests were too easy.</P><P>Trust me I couldn't be happier that they increased the drop on the cape. I just think there is problems with quests in eq. And I think alot of people would agree with me on this.</P><P>btw, here is what I said in my previous post word for word...</P><P>"Camping something, or raiding something and hoping for a random drop doesn't seem to constitute a well thought out quest."</P><P>I never once said camping a three day spawn was a challenge or a good thing. If anything I was hoping to lean more towards the tone of, camping is mind numbingly painful and more an excersise in futility then anything else. and due to camping being the only way VI seems to know how to make things rare, this leads to there being inherent problems imo in the quests of EQ.</P><P>Hopefully this post will explain myself a bit more and show that I'm really not full of envy :)</P><P>Gylgesh Gloomtouch,<BR>54th Necro of the Heroic Few<BR>Morell-Thule<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
